==English==
===Etymology===
From the name of the inventor, Robert Atkins.

===Noun phrase===
'''Atkins diet''' (''uncountable'')

#(''with'' '''the''') A [[diet]] in which a person loses weight reducing his or her intake of [[carbohydrate]]s, thereby obtaining energy from [[dietary]] and stored [[fat]].
#:''I've lost ten pounds since I started the Atkins diet''

